                <div class="collapse" id="collapseArticle3">
                  <div class="card card-body">
                  <p>Following my first assessment I started working on Module 2. It became clear to me after a few assignments that the 2nd Module will be much more challenging than the Programming Fundamentals module. Module two started with the introduction of React and why we use it. It was interesting to learn about all the different frameworks and libraries.</p>
                  <img src="images/rva.jpeg" class="img-fluid"></img>
                  <br>
                  <p>Comparing Angular, React and Vue gave me a better understanding of what is out there in the industry. Each one of them has it’s pros and cons. It became evident very quickly when making research on both React and Angular that they are the most used in todays world. Mastering one of them is good, but I am sure that becoming an expert in both of them would definitely be a big asset to have. I will definitely have Angular on my list to learn for the future. I am not going to discuss the pros and cons of the above mentioned libraries and frameworks in this story. There are enough stories out there that will give you a good overview. However if you are interested in learning more about React, Angular and Vue check out this article. It really helped me out to grasp the differences.
                      <a href="https://medium.com/@TechMagic/reactjs-vs-angular5-vs-vue-js-what-to-choose-in-2018-b91e028fa91d"target="_blank">"Article-Link."</a> 
                  </p>
                  <p>
                      The first project that I worked on in Module 2 was Bloc-Jams-React. This app gave me the first taste of what it means to use a library such as React and create a SPA(single page application). You could quickly see that React’s virtual DOM helps the front end side to perform in a fast manner. I obviously ran into problems, but the support staff through Slack and my mentor really helped out when I was stuck. If you are interested in checking out my project, have a look here:
                  </p>
                  <img src="images/Jam-NM.jpg" class="img-fluid"></img>
                  <br>
                  <p>Following Bloc-Jams-React app I worked on my second project. The second project was Bloc-Chat-React which was also my first encounter with Firebase.</p>
                  <img src="images/Firebase.png" class="img-fluid" style="width:50%"></img>
                  <br>
                  <p>Firebase is a Backend as a Service provided by google. I had to learn implementing firebase, because of it’s google authentication and data storage service. This project was much more challenging than the first one, because the checkpoint had barley any code examples. So it was mostly on me to make my own research and learn how firebase works. I haven’t finished the design of the project yet, but I will post it in my future stories.</p>
                  <p>After the two projects it was time to demonstrate my skills and knowledge in my second assessment. I prepared for a week and the second assessment required you to have a deeper understanding of Javascript, CSS3 and HTML. It also covered a few questions about React. It was nerve recking, but I passed the assessment and it felt awesome. I have learned so much in a short period of time and I can’t wait to see what’s next in Module 3. It will definitely not become easier, but I am looking very forward to learn more about Data Structures, Algorithms, Databases and SQL in the next Module.</p>
                  <p>Overall my experience has been super positive with Bloc. I have made some great process over a short period of time and can’t wait to see where this journey is going to take me. I will stop here for now and will try to post an update again in the near future. Until then happy hacking everyone!!!</p>

